race.comment: SCOUNDREL (2) racing in career best form. Dominant winner two-back, before closing strongly with the 58.5kg when third over 1600m at Gatton. Maps to stalk the speed and hard to stop in this vein of form. WHISKEY MISS (10) strengthened over the break and the blinkers come off fourth-up. Went back from the draw and returned good closing splits when a close-up fourth over 1420m at Grafton. Poorly drawn again and will keep improving as she gets out further in trip. IN THE FINE PRINT (5) improving gelding with the two wins from his last four starts. Launched late when a narrow winner over 1612m at Coffs Harbour. Apprentice goes on today and gets his chance from the low gate. SISTINE CHAPEL (9) holding her form and doesn't have to improve much to win this. Edged out late when second over 1540m at the Gold Coast Poly. Each way contender.
